The thread dump plugin bundled with Confluence 3.0 and higher does not (and cannot) produce output that can be analyzed (CONF-18529).  We need to move the instructions for the thread dump plugin to a KB article ("How to take a thread dump when kill -3 doesn't work") and revert the wording of these pages to favor manual thread dumps:

http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF30/Generating+a+Thread+Dump
http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Generating%20a%20Thread%20Dump

For further details, please liase with Partha.  Here's his comment on the matter:

{quote}
I think we should remove from the docs, instructions about generating a thread dump via confluence and move these instructions to the FAQ with a heading like "How to provide thread dumps when you cannot kill -3" or something like that. 

There have been occasions when I haven't been able to get thread dumps due to some restrictions on the customers side, and these stack trace dumps have really made things easy. 

I understand that they can be frustrating to read, but trust me they are hell of lot easier than trying to work out performance related issues where the customer cannot get a proper thread dump. 
{quote}

