When using many macros in a page it can get hard to keep track of where an enclosing macro is opening and where it is closing.

Case in point: {section}{column}col A{column}{column}col B{column}{section}

It would be nice if the Confluence allowed the macro syntax to start with {/ without breaking. That is {/foo} would be equivalent to {foo}. This would help those of us that are familiar with html-syntax to mark up the above example as:

{section}{column}col A{/column}{column}col B{/column}{/section}

I do not suggest systematic enforcement of any kind. This feature would only be a "crutch" for those users that choose to use it, with the system tolerant of errors in usage. 

Any erroneous markup by improper closing should then cause no problems :{/foo}inside{foo}outside{foo}inside{/foo}
(except for the user trying to make sense of it)

