The configuration we use in server.xml looks like this:
{code}
        <Connector className="org.apache.coyote.tomcat4.CoyoteConnector" port="8080" minProcessors="5"
                   maxProcessors="75"
                   enableLookups="false" redirectPort="8443" acceptCount="10" debug="0" connectionTimeout="20000"
                   useURIValidationHack="false" URIEncoding="UTF-8"/>
{code}

While it's not causing any problem at the moment, I believe we should be moving to the newer version of the connector. 

Apache has removed reference to Tomcat 4's documentation from [its home page|http://tomcat.apache.org/], making it difficult to search information about the connector despite that they are [still exist|http://tomcat.apache.org/tomcat-4.1-doc/config/connectors.html].

We should move to [Tomcat 6's connector|http://tomcat.apache.org/tomcat-6.0-doc/connectors.html].

